      "h": "Settler Motivations and Conflicts",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> Anglo-American settlers were a growing population in Texas whose economic interests and cultural values often conflicted with Mexican law, contributing to rising tensions.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from en.wikipedia.org; tshaonline.org. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Settlers came mainly from the southern United States seeking land and opportunity</li><li>Many brought enslaved people despite Mexican laws against slavery</li><li>Settlers established communities with distinct cultural and political views</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>Stephen F. Austin led the first large group of settlers into Texas under Mexican permission.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Why might settlers resist Mexican laws, especially regarding slavery?</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Assuming settlers fully accepted Mexican authority or culture.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> en.wikipedia.org; tshaonline.org <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p>"
