    "num": "09",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Key Players</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">William Travis, James Bowie, and Davy Crockett: Defenders of the Alamo</h2><ul><li>Travis was the commander of Texian forces at the Alamo</li><li>Bowie was a skilled frontiersman and co-commander</li><li>Crockett was a famed American folk hero and volunteer</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">These leaders became symbols of Texian resistance during the Siege of the Alamo, where a small force held out against a much larger Mexican army. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Travis’s famous letter calling for reinforcements became a rallying cry.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss the significance of the Alamo defenders’ sacrifice.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming the Alamo was a military victory rather than a symbolic defeat.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide9\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which group primarily settled Texas under Mexican rule and contributed to tensions leading to the war?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;Anglo-American settlers&quot;,&quot;French colonists&quot;,&quot;Spanish soldiers&quot;,&quot;Native American tribes&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;Anglo-American settlers played a major role in Texas&#39;s demographic and political tensions under Mexican governance.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain the significance of the Texas War of Independence in shaping the region&#39;s history.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should include causes such as political and cultural tensions under Mexican rule, key events like the Siege of the Alamo and Battle of San Jacinto, major figures involved, and outcomes including the establishment of the Republic of Texas.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;The Texas War of Independence was significant because it marked Texas&#39;s break from Mexican rule due to political and cultural conflicts. Key events like the Siege of the Alamo symbolized Texian resistance, and the Battle of San Jacinto secured victory. Leaders like Sam Houston were crucial, and the war led to the creation of the Republic of Texas.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;It led to Texas gaining independence from Mexico&quot;,&quot;Key battles like the Alamo and San Jacinto were important&quot;,&quot;Sam Houston and other leaders played major roles&quot;,&quot;It resulted in the Republic of Texas being established&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
