    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">10</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Key Players</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">General Antonio López de Santa Anna: Mexican Leader</h2><ul><li>President and general of Mexico during the Texas Revolution</li><li>Centralized power, provoking resistance in Texas and other regions</li><li>Led Mexican forces in key battles including the Alamo and San Jacinto</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Santa Anna was a dominant figure whose policies and military actions directly influenced the outbreak and course of the Texas War of Independence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> His decision to personally lead troops into Texas escalated the conflict.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate Santa Anna’s leadership decisions and their consequences.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Portraying Santa Anna only as a villain without understanding his political context.</p></div></div>",
