    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">22</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Perspectives: Analyzing Primary Sources</h2><ul><li>Examine excerpts from the Texas Declaration of Independence</li><li>Identify language reflecting political and cultural views</li><li>Consider how different groups might interpret the text</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Analyzing primary sources like the Texas Declaration helps learners understand the motivations and perspectives of those involved in the revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s14\">[14]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The declaration’s emphasis on 'tyranny' reflects Texian views of Santa Anna’s government.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Read a provided excerpt and identify key grievances and their implications.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Taking historical documents at face value without considering context or bias.</p></div></div>",
