    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">23</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Transfer</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Connecting the Texas Revolution to Broader Themes</h2><ul><li>Compare Texas independence to other revolutions</li><li>Explore themes of self-determination and sovereignty</li><li>Consider the role of cultural identity in conflicts</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas Revolution shares similarities with other independence movements, highlighting universal themes of political freedom and cultural conflict. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Like the American Revolution, Texans cited grievances and sought self-governance.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify similarities and differences between the Texas Revolution and another independence movement you know.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming all revolutions have the same causes and outcomes.</p></div></div>",
