    "num": "24",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">24</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Transfer</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Reflecting on the Significance of the Texas War of Independence</h2><ul><li>Shaped Texas’s political and cultural identity</li><li>Influenced U.S.-Mexico relations and territorial expansion</li><li>Raised questions about rights, sovereignty, and inclusion</li><li>Legacy continues in Texas and American history</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas War of Independence had lasting impacts on regional politics, culture, and the broader history of the United States and Mexico. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The Republic of Texas eventually joined the U.S., contributing to tensions leading to the Mexican-American War.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a short reflection on why the Texas Revolution remains important today.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing the war as an isolated event without broader consequences.</p></div></div>",
