      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> The Texas War of Independence had lasting impacts on regional politics, culture, and the broader history of the United States and Mexico.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from en.wikipedia.org; southern.libguides.com; en.wikipedia.org. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Shaped Texas’s political and cultural identity</li><li>Influenced U.S.-Mexico relations and territorial expansion</li><li>Raised questions about rights, sovereignty, and inclusion</li><li>Legacy continues in Texas and American history</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>The Republic of Texas eventually joined the U.S., contributing to tensions leading to the Mexican-American War.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Write a short reflection on why the Texas Revolution remains important today.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Viewing the war as an isolated event without broader consequences.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> en.wikipedia.org; southern.libguides.com; en.wikipedia.org <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p>"
