    "id": "slide28",
    "eyebrow": "Establishment and Constitution",
    "num": "28",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Establishment and Constitution</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Forming the Republic of Texas: Government Structure</h2><ul><li>Declared independence March 1836, formed a republic</li><li>Constitution modeled on U.S. system with executive, legislative, judiciary</li><li>Sam Houston elected first president</li><li>Focused on establishing law, order, and defense</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">After winning independence, Texas established itself as a republic with a government structure inspired by the United States. This new government aimed to create stability and legitimacy for the fledgling nation. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The Republic’s constitution included checks and balances similar to the U.S. Constitution, reflecting Texians’ American heritage.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Describe one way the Republic of Texas government was similar to the U.S. government and one way it was different.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texas immediately became a U.S. state rather than an independent republic first.</p></div></div>",
    "paper": {
      "secnum": "Deep Dive 28",
      "h": "Deep Dive: The Republic of Texas Constitution and Governance",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> After winning independence, Texas established itself as a republic with a government structure inspired by the United States. This new government aimed to create stability and legitimacy for the fledgling nation.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from southern.libguides.com; dp.la. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Declared independence March 1836, formed a republic</li><li>Constitution modeled on U.S. system with executive, legislative, judiciary</li><li>Sam Houston elected first president</li><li>Focused on establishing law, order, and defense</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>The Republic’s constitution included checks and balances similar to the U.S. Constitution, reflecting Texians’ American heritage.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Describe one way the Republic of Texas government was similar to the U.S. government and one way it was different.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Assuming Texas immediately became a U.S. state rather than an independent republic first.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> southern.libguides.com; dp.la <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p>"
    }
