    "id": "slide33",
    "eyebrow": "Practice and Checks",
    "num": "33",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">33</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice and Checks</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Check Your Understanding: Key Battles</h2><ul><li>When did the Siege of the Alamo occur?</li><li>Who led the Texian forces at San Jacinto?</li><li>What was the outcome of the Battle of San Jacinto?</li><li>Why is ‘Remember the Alamo!’ significant?</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This checkpoint assesses learners’ recall and comprehension of major battles and their significance in the Texas War of Independence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Answer: The Siege of the Alamo occurred in early 1836; Sam Houston led at San Jacinto; the battle resulted in Texian victory and Santa Anna’s capture; the phrase motivated Texian forces.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Answer the questions and explain why each is important to understanding the war.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Confusing dates or leaders, or missing the symbolic importance of battles.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide33\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which group primarily settled Texas under Mexican rule and contributed to tensions leading to the war?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;Anglo-American settlers&quot;,&quot;French colonists&quot;,&quot;Spanish soldiers&quot;,&quot;Native American tribes&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;Anglo-American settlers played a major role in Texas&#39;s demographic and political tensions under Mexican governance.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain the significance of the Texas War of Independence in shaping the region&#39;s history.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should include causes such as political and cultural tensions under Mexican rule, key events like the Siege of the Alamo and Battle of San Jacinto, major figures involved, and outcomes including the establishment of the Republic of Texas.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;The Texas War of Independence was significant because it marked Texas&#39;s break from Mexican rule due to political and cultural conflicts. Key events like the Siege of the Alamo symbolized Texian resistance, and the Battle of San Jacinto secured victory. Leaders like Sam Houston were crucial, and the war led to the creation of the Republic of Texas.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;It led to Texas gaining independence from Mexico&quot;,&quot;Key battles like the Alamo and San Jacinto were important&quot;,&quot;Sam Houston and other leaders played major roles&quot;,&quot;It resulted in the Republic of Texas being established&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
    "paper": {
      "secnum": "Deep Dive 33",
      "h": "Deep Dive: Connecting Battles to War Outcomes",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> This checkpoint assesses learners’ recall and comprehension of major battles and their significance in the Texas War of Independence.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from en.wikipedia.org; southern.libguides.com; gilderlehrman.org. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>When did the Siege of the Alamo occur?</li><li>Who led the Texian forces at San Jacinto?</li><li>What was the outcome of the Battle of San Jacinto?</li><li>Why is ‘Remember the Alamo!’ significant?</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>Answer: The Siege of the Alamo occurred in early 1836; Sam Houston led at San Jacinto; the battle resulted in Texian victory and Santa Anna’s capture; the phrase motivated Texian forces.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Answer the questions and explain why each is important to understanding the war.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Confusing dates or leaders, or missing the symbolic importance of battles.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> en.wikipedia.org; southern.libguides.com; gilderlehrman.org <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p>"
    }
