    "eyebrow": "Transfer",
    "num": "35",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">35</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Transfer</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Connecting the Texas Revolution to Broader Themes</h2><ul><li>Compare Texas independence with other 19th-century revolutions</li><li>Explore themes of self-determination and national identity</li><li>Discuss the role of cultural conflict in political change</li><li>Consider lasting impacts on U.S.-Mexico relations</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">By connecting the Texas Revolution to wider historical themes, learners can transfer knowledge and deepen understanding of independence movements and cultural dynamics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Similarities exist between Texas and other revolutions, such as appeals to rights and resistance to central authority.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify one way the Texas Revolution is similar to or different from another independence movement.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overgeneralizing or ignoring unique local factors in comparisons.</p></div></div>",
    "paper": {
      "secnum": "Deep Dive 35",
      "h": "Deep Dive: The Texas Revolution in Global Context",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> By connecting the Texas Revolution to wider historical themes, learners can transfer knowledge and deepen understanding of independence movements and cultural dynamics.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from en.wikipedia.org; billofrightsinstitute.org; tshaonline.org. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Compare Texas independence with other 19th-century revolutions</li><li>Explore themes of self-determination and national identity</li><li>Discuss the role of cultural conflict in political change</li><li>Consider lasting impacts on U.S.-Mexico relations</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>Similarities exist between Texas and other revolutions, such as appeals to rights and resistance to central authority.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Identify one way the Texas Revolution is similar to or different from another independence movement.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Overgeneralizing or ignoring unique local factors in comparisons.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> en.wikipedia.org; billofrightsinstitute.org; tshaonline.org <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p>"
    },
