    "id": "slide36",
    "eyebrow": "Reflection",
    "num": "36",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">36</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Reflection</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Reflecting on the Significance of the Texas War of Independence</h2><ul><li>Marked the birth of the Republic of Texas</li><li>Set stage for U.S. annexation and future conflicts</li><li>Symbolized struggles over rights, identity, and power</li><li>Remains a key event in Texas and American history</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas War of Independence was a transformative event with lasting political, social, and cultural effects. Reflecting on its significance helps learners synthesize knowledge and appreciate its complexity. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The war’s legacy includes Texas’s unique identity and ongoing debates about its causes and consequences.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief reflection on why the Texas War of Independence matters today.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing the war only as a simple victory or loss without considering broader impacts.</p></div></div>",
